      "content": "i mean i get that there are still issues, but some people say the whole movement's focus on things like non-violence and specific legislative goals was actually what made it successful, while others argue those tactics were actually pretty limited or even counterproductive compared to more radical approaches. how do historians actually view the effectiveness of those different strategies?",
